1
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:07,632
Are we getting closer?

2
00:00:08,758 --> 00:00:09,675
Room 202.

3
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:11,593
- It's by the entrance.
- Okay.

4
00:00:11,594 --> 00:00:12,553
I'm scared.

5
00:00:12,554 --> 00:00:14,221
- Exactly.
- Even this corridor is scary.

6
00:00:14,222 --> 00:00:15,806
My heart nearly stopped.

7
00:00:15,807 --> 00:00:17,099
I really hate ghosts.

8
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:20,185
A heart attack doesn't come that easy.

9
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:21,895
I've done my part for today.

10
00:00:21,896 --> 00:00:23,397
- You're done?
- Yes, I'm done.

11
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:24,982
- My desired…
- Lee to the rescue?

12
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:26,401
Yes, I did my fair share.

13
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,863
- Okay.
- There are shapes like this.

14
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:37,162
All the houses are drawn diagonally.

15
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:40,622
A KEY CARD WITH A GRAY ANGULAR PATTERN

16
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:42,958
Maybe it goes over the white blocks.

17
00:00:42,959 --> 00:00:44,209
Should we try it?

18
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:45,336
Try it, Karina.

19
00:00:46,546 --> 00:00:48,630
Maybe flip the card upside down?

20
00:00:48,631 --> 00:00:50,132
LINES UP THE KEY CARD ON THE PUZZLE

21
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,383
Does anything match?

22
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:53,511
If you line it up like this…

23
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:55,387
LINES UP THE SHARP EDGES

24
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:56,889
That fits.

25
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:58,932
Maybe it's the number of windows?

26
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:00,809
How do we match them perfectly?

27
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:04,813
- Maybe it's these houses?
- We have to figure that out.

28
00:01:04,814 --> 00:01:07,108
That's 438.

29
00:01:08,526 --> 00:01:12,529
- If we line it up like this, 433…
- It's 4338.

30
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:13,364
Try it.

31
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:18,827
WRONG

32
00:01:18,828 --> 00:01:20,871
- That's not it.
- It's not?

33
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:22,874
- What if we rotate it?
- Vertically?

34
00:01:24,501 --> 00:01:26,168
I think we had it right the first time.

35
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:27,461
- It was like this, right?
- Yes.

36
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:33,675
I think we need to focus
on the buildings with slanted roofs.

37
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:36,386
So, that's 4, 12, 3, and 8.

38
00:01:36,387 --> 00:01:38,222
- It could be five digits.
- That's true.

39
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:40,098
IS IT A FIVE-DIGIT PASSCODE THIS TIME?

40
00:01:40,099 --> 00:01:41,100
It's 41238?

41
00:01:44,145 --> 00:01:45,563
WRONG

42
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:47,648
SIGH

43
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:51,319
But why doesn't it line up perfectly?

44
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,363
I wish it lined up neater.

45
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:57,074
- Does it not?
- These parts don't line up.

46
00:01:57,075 --> 00:01:58,992
It's a little off.

47
00:01:58,993 --> 00:02:01,829
This should show us something.

48
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:04,207
For example,
that could be the number eight.

49
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,335
And this could be a three.

50
00:02:08,586 --> 00:02:10,212
I think that's how it works.

51
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:14,884
- We need to create a 3D image.
- You're right. That makes sense.

52
00:02:16,052 --> 00:02:17,010
Should we step back?

53
00:02:17,011 --> 00:02:19,972
VIEWS FROM A DISTANCE

54
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:23,560
MOVING AROUND

55
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:27,063
Wait, move it up.

56
00:02:29,065 --> 00:02:31,400
- There's something there, right?
- There is.

57
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:33,694
It does look like numbers.

58
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:35,779
- Nine.
- Nine, three…

59
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:37,614
- Nine, three…
- Nine, three?

60
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:38,991
One and eight?

61
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:42,077
ENTERING 9318 WITHOUT HESITATION

62
00:02:42,078 --> 00:02:43,370
WRONG

63
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:45,789
- Go back to where Hye-ri was, John.
- Where?

64
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:46,999
<i>- The place we started.
- Here?</i>

65
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,293
<i>Yes, a bit higher.</i>

66
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:52,045
- Like this?
- Yes, that's it.

67
00:02:52,046 --> 00:02:53,714
There it is.

68
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,966
I told you. There it is!

69
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:58,803
- It's 3732.
- That's where it was.

70
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,973
ROOM 202 IS OPEN AT LAST

71
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:04,642
Let's go in.

72
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:08,021
- If it wasn't for you, we'd all be dead.
- Seriously.

73
00:03:08,605 --> 00:03:10,647
ENTERING ROOM 202

74
00:03:10,648 --> 00:03:12,566
- I'm too scared to do this.
- This is cool.

75
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,443
What could this be?

76
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:17,404
It was a mini golf course.

77
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:19,406
There were six strings.

78
00:03:19,407 --> 00:03:25,537
They met at the center,
where a hook was attached.

79
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:27,247
It was like a model house.

80
00:03:27,248 --> 00:03:32,878
It looked like the miniature models
used for apartment construction plans.

81
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:34,421
It was like a 3D blueprint.

82
00:03:34,422 --> 00:03:36,298
There were six fishing rods.

83
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:38,342
So, I knew we had to work together.

84
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:40,260
- This is…
- Is this a group mission?

85
00:03:40,261 --> 00:03:42,721
I think we have to move the balls.

86
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:45,474
- You have to adjust the strings to do it.
- I see.

87
00:03:45,475 --> 00:03:46,516
That's it.

88
00:03:46,517 --> 00:03:49,686
- That's how we put them in the red hole.
- Okay.

89
00:03:49,687 --> 00:03:51,688
Okay, it's like a claw machine.

90
00:03:51,689 --> 00:03:53,608
That's a magnet, right?

91
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:56,944
- We use it to pick up the red ball.
- Okay.

92
00:03:56,945 --> 00:03:58,612
- Should we put it in the red hole?
- Yes.

93
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:00,072
- Let's try that.
- If it doesn't work…

94
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:01,365
- Let's give it a go.
- All right.

95
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:03,617
- Should we all loosen the strings?
- Sure.

96
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:05,410
- Loosen it?
- Yes.

97
00:04:05,411 --> 00:04:06,913
- Yong-jin, pull your string.
- Okay.

98
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,374
- Oh, there are two balls.
- Be gentle.

99
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,209
- Yong-jin, pull harder.
- Pull it a bit more.

100
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:13,919
Should I pull harder too?

101
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,546
- I'm getting worked up.
- Hye-ri, can you loosen yours?

102
00:04:16,547 --> 00:04:17,547
Yes, it's working.

103
00:04:17,548 --> 00:04:18,548
- We did it.
- We did it.

104
00:04:18,549 --> 00:04:19,716
- Is it a magnet?
- Lift it up?

105
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:21,009
- Is it not?
- I guess not.

106
00:04:21,010 --> 00:04:22,135
Is it not?

107
00:04:22,136 --> 00:04:23,679
- Don't tell me.
- It's a magnet, right?

108
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,763
Let's lift it.

109
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:26,265
- It's not a magnet.
- It's not.

110
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:27,641
- It's not?
- Aim for the center.

111
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:30,018
- We need to roll it.
- That must be it.

112
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:31,436
- This is too hard.
- Really?

113
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:32,771
So that's what we have to do.

114
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:35,107
We can hit the ball
by tugging the strings.

115
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:37,276
This would be hard even with a magnet.

116
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,819
This is crazy.

117
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:39,946
This is so hard.

118
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:42,155
- It's so hard.
- Are you kidding?

119
00:04:42,156 --> 00:04:43,824
How can that not be a magnet?

120
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:44,783
That's so unfair.

121
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:48,078
I thought maybe the magnet had fallen off.

122
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:51,164
I thought the magnet must have fallen off

123
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:53,125
because we pulled the strings wrong.

124
00:04:53,126 --> 00:04:55,085
<i>It was just too hard.</i>

125
00:04:55,086 --> 00:04:58,046
- The direction is most important.
- Yes.

126
00:04:58,047 --> 00:05:01,133
- We're paired up diagonally, right?
- That's right.

127
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:04,553
- That's the key to finding a balance.
- Exactly.

128
00:05:04,554 --> 00:05:06,179
If I pull the string…

129
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:08,015
- He loosens it.
- Right.

130
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:11,476
The key is working
with the person on the other side.

131
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:13,895
- Okay, let's try.
- If we…

132
00:05:13,896 --> 00:05:16,356
- Should we try moving this way?
- Okay.

133
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:18,400
- If Gabee pulls…
- I'll pull it.

134
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:20,694
- And you loosen it, Karina.
- I'm done.

135
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:23,238
I'll pull it up with you.

136
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:25,657
- Hye-ri, can you loosen yours?
- That's right.

137
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:27,993
- Yes, just like this.
- We need to let it loose.

138
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:29,286
Do it slowly.

139
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:30,996
Hye-ri, loosen it a bit more.

140
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:32,331
I think this will work.

141
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:33,166
Look.

142
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:38,462
- We can do this.
- We've got this.

143
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:40,047
- It's too hard.
- Can we do this?

144
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:41,506
It was too hard.

145
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:44,092
There were limits to what you could do.

146
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:45,802
We had to work with the person across.

147
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:48,180
Even then,
the string only moved in one direction.

148
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:49,639
To get the ball over there,

149
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:51,683
all six agents had to work together.

150
00:05:51,684 --> 00:05:53,769
That was the only way to do it.

151
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:55,312
Am I in a key position?

152
00:05:55,313 --> 00:05:56,438
Someone switch with me.

153
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:57,732
CONFIDENCE DROPPED

154
00:05:58,775 --> 00:05:59,609
Should I hit it?

155
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,027
BANG

156
00:06:03,112 --> 00:06:04,654
Something fell off.

157
00:06:04,655 --> 00:06:07,574
- What?
- The tip fell off.

158
00:06:07,575 --> 00:06:08,618
PROPERTY DAMAGE

159
00:06:09,368 --> 00:06:10,869
Is this even possible?

160
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:12,496
Should we press F1 key?

161
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:14,331
Yes, we should.

162
00:06:14,332 --> 00:06:15,582
Isn't it worth trying?

163
00:06:15,583 --> 00:06:18,668
- Yes, we might be wrong.
- I agree.

164
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:20,463
What else could it be?

165
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:23,632
I had a feeling
the F1 key would be useless.

166
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:28,136
I thought it would just say,
"Try harder! Good luck! Stay calm!"

167
00:06:28,137 --> 00:06:31,306
It wasn't going to give us the answer.

168
00:06:31,307 --> 00:06:33,850
What hint could it give us?

169
00:06:33,851 --> 00:06:35,685
Isn't it obvious
that we have to put it in there?

170
00:06:35,686 --> 00:06:37,312
- That's true.
- Let's just try it.

171
00:06:37,313 --> 00:06:38,648
It seems a bit too simple for that.

172
00:06:39,398 --> 00:06:40,650
Can this be done?

173
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,026
We're losing so much time.

174
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:44,236
THE GAUGE HAS DROPPED

175
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:45,654
When did it get so low?

176
00:06:45,655 --> 00:06:46,988
Let's go! It's mind over matter.

177
00:06:46,989 --> 00:06:48,198
Why are you all down?

178
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,616
Yes, it's mind over matter.

179
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:51,618
Here we go. Aim for the red ball.

180
00:06:51,619 --> 00:06:52,453
Here we go.

181
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:54,746
- I'll loosen mine.
- Okay.

182
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:56,289
Let's go slowly. We've got this.

183
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:59,709
Come on.
All of us are stars in this industry.

184
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:00,710
- Does that matter?
- Yes.

185
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:02,587
- Don't fall apart now.
- Stay strong!

186
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:03,588
You're right.

187
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:05,132
We're all stars.

188
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:09,427
- Let's go. We can do this.
- We're all stars in some way.

189
00:07:09,428 --> 00:07:11,721
- Look at that, my friends!
- There we go.

190
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:13,557
- Here we go!
- We're going great.

191
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:15,767
- We can do this. We got it to…
- Wait.

192
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:18,562
- We can't let it go slack.
- You're right.

193
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:21,106
- Keep the string tight.
- I'll loosen mine.

194
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,691
You also have to pull.

195
00:07:22,692 --> 00:07:23,984
- Pull tighter.
- It's working.

196
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,610
- Good job, Karina.
- We need to keep it up.

197
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:27,028
We're doing great. Move slowly.

198
00:07:27,029 --> 00:07:28,655
Karina, pull back a little.

199
00:07:28,656 --> 00:07:31,825
Let's not lose heart even if we mess up.

200
00:07:31,826 --> 00:07:33,285
Of course, Yong-jin.

201
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:36,037
- Gabee, pull back a bit.
- I'll pull a bit more.

202
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:37,205
I'll be so disappointed.

203
00:07:37,206 --> 00:07:38,540
Don't be!

204
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:40,208
Let's stay positive.

205
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:42,003
We're doing great. It's looking good.

206
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:43,837
So far, so good.

207
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:45,922
- Let's go.
- It's looking good.

208
00:07:45,923 --> 00:07:48,301
John, can you tug it a bit?

209
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:52,220
Pull it.

210
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:53,805
- Please.
- Okay, we can do it.

211
00:07:53,806 --> 00:07:55,724
- Yong-jin, could you…
- We're killing it.

212
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:57,435
- You want me to pull back?
- Can you try?

213
00:07:58,227 --> 00:08:01,021
There you go. It's lying flat.
This is more stable.

214
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:02,106
Now, pull it that way.

215
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:06,359
Damn it.

216
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:08,446
- The ball went up there.
- Hold on.

217
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:11,031
- It went up there.
- They're both stuck in the corner.

218
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:11,948
This is…

219
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:13,284
Is there a reset button?

220
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,953
Sorry, I got a bit disappointed.

221
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:18,705
Sorry, I'm a bit tired.

222
00:08:18,706 --> 00:08:20,790
I need to own up to it.

223
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:22,502
How is this harder than a hole-in-one?

224
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:25,420
I'm never playing golf again.

225
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:27,797
It made us want to give up

226
00:08:27,798 --> 00:08:31,009
because we used all our energy to focus,
and then, we'd lose it.

227
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:34,054
TO MAKE MATTERS WORSE,
THE RED BALLS ARE STUCK IN THE CORNER

228
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:34,971
Unbelievable.

229
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:37,766
What happened to being agents?

230
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:40,061
This is so frustrating.

231
00:08:41,562 --> 00:08:42,522
Guess what?

232
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:46,399
- You've got it, John.
- It's working.

233
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,235
- That's it.
- Good job.

234
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,154
- We're almost there.
- That's it.

235
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:51,821
That's it.

236
00:08:51,822 --> 00:08:52,989
THEY GOT ONE RED BALL OUT

237
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:54,533
- We got one out.
- All right.

238
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:56,576
- We'll get to that later.
- Let's begin.

239
00:08:56,577 --> 00:08:57,744
Let's get to work.

240
00:08:57,745 --> 00:08:58,995
Should we loosen it a bit?

241
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:02,123
- Let's get to work.
- I think we only need one in, not two.

242
00:09:02,124 --> 00:09:03,625
If we have to get both in,

243
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:05,210
we'll be here
until the day after tomorrow.

244
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:06,628
It can't be done.

245
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:09,756
One thing's for sure.
We've got a handle on it.

246
00:09:09,757 --> 00:09:11,216
- We improved.
- We know what we're doing.

247
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:13,260
Let's not win angrily.

248
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:15,346
- Let's win with a smile.
- You're right.

249
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,556
Okay, we can do this.

250
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:21,893
We have a feel for this now.
We've got this now, right?

251
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:23,270
We can…

252
00:09:23,271 --> 00:09:24,397
- That's okay.
- Of course.

253
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:27,107
This is no big deal.

254
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:28,275
It's no big deal.

255
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:32,529
- Who's a good one?
- Hold on.

256
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:33,822
Look at that.

257
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:35,156
- Okay.
- Goodness.

258
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:36,867
- Focus.
- Yes.

259
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:38,827
Move slowly.

260
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,078
I'm letting go little by little.

261
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:42,123
- Little by little.
- That's great.

262
00:09:47,753 --> 00:09:48,962
Oh, wait.

263
00:09:48,963 --> 00:09:50,463
A CLOSE CALL

264
00:09:50,464 --> 00:09:52,507
- That's good. It's lying flat.
- From here…

265
00:09:52,508 --> 00:09:54,968
- There's another incline here.
- Yes.

266
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:57,762
You know we all knew that already, right?

267
00:09:57,763 --> 00:10:00,473
YONG-JIN IS NOT ANNOYED AT ALL

268
00:10:00,474 --> 00:10:02,142
- Let's do this.
- Let's get it this time.

269
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:03,518
Let's stick together.

270
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:05,061
I'll loosen that. You take over.

271
00:10:05,062 --> 00:10:06,689
I think that's better. I'll do…

272
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:08,773
A CLOSE CALL

273
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:09,733
ALMOST SLIPPED

274
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:10,650
Okay, don't worry.

275
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:12,193
You can do this, red ball.

276
00:10:12,194 --> 00:10:14,487
- We can do this. Let's go home.
- Yes, of course.

277
00:10:14,488 --> 00:10:15,615
I'M NOT LEAVING

278
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:18,700
It keeps rolling away.

279
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:20,160
Is this a real game?

280
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:21,328
Hey, friends.

281
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:23,997
We've been through worse.

282
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:25,290
- You're right.
- Right?

283
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,499
This is nothing.

284
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,793
- We're getting better.
- This is no big deal.

285
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:30,337
I can't believe I'm getting better.

286
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:32,756
What are you doing, Do-hoon?
Grab your fishing rod.

287
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:34,924
- I've turned over a new leaf.
- Get to it.

288
00:10:34,925 --> 00:10:36,134
Let's do this. Let's go.

289
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:37,177
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

290
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:38,012
Let's go!

291
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:40,221
FAIL

292
00:10:40,222 --> 00:10:42,098
- Let's do this.
- Let's go!

293
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:44,768
SAY IT LOUDER, LET'S GO!

294
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:47,354
FAIL

295
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:49,606
UNTIL THE END, LET'S GO!

296
00:10:49,607 --> 00:10:51,232
This little rascal…

297
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:52,150
Go slowly.

298
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:55,862
- Is this right?
- I want to smash it.

299
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:58,198
SIGH

300
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:00,158
You'll see the cut-down version.

301
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:02,661
But we know how long it took.

302
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:03,578
It was really…

303
00:11:03,579 --> 00:11:05,288
I think it'll fall down. No, stop.

304
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:07,332
No, stop. We need to lower it.

305
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,417
Stop.

306
00:11:09,293 --> 00:11:11,503
- I'm losing my mind.
- It's so frustrating.

307
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:13,546
1 HOUR LATER

308
00:11:13,547 --> 00:11:15,632
I wanted to smash that glass.

309
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:16,591
Seriously.

310
00:11:16,592 --> 00:11:20,053
CONSUMING RAGE

311
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:22,597
This is the toughest thing
I've done in the last five years.

312
00:11:22,598 --> 00:11:24,057
Let's not get worked up.

313
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:25,850
We should smile.

314
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:27,519
Let's stay calm.

315
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:28,812
Wait a minute.

316
00:11:28,813 --> 00:11:29,854
What if we…

317
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:32,607
Let go of your string, Karina.
Let go of it completely.

318
00:11:32,608 --> 00:11:33,942
It has to go up like this.

319
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:36,027
We need to tilt it like this.

320
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:36,986
- I see.
- Right?

321
00:11:36,987 --> 00:11:38,863
- We should do it on the slope.
- Right.

322
00:11:38,864 --> 00:11:40,073
- Do you get it?
- Yes.

323
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:41,991
- We've cracked it.
- Okay.

324
00:11:41,992 --> 00:11:44,369
We'll get it in two tries.

325
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:45,870
- I hope so.
- I'm sure.

326
00:11:45,871 --> 00:11:48,081
- We've got this.
- We just need to go slower.

327
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:49,249
- Slowly.
- Yes.

328
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:51,251
FIRST SLOPE REACHED

329
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:54,462
What matters here is the angle

330
00:11:54,463 --> 00:11:55,797
and how much we tilt it.

331
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:56,798
PRECISE ANGLE CONTROL

332
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:57,757
That's right.

333
00:11:57,758 --> 00:12:00,009
- We're doing great.
- We are.

334
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:03,513
STEADY ASCENT

335
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:05,974
Let's go a bit slower.

336
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:07,684
We need to tilt it.

337
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:09,686
Yes, keep it steady.

338
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:10,603
That's it.

339
00:12:10,604 --> 00:12:13,565
SECOND SLOPE REACHED

340
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:14,941
We have to tilt it.

341
00:12:14,942 --> 00:12:16,277
Just tilt it slightly like that.

342
00:12:17,486 --> 00:12:18,612
It has to be at that angle.

343
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:22,323
We need to shift it towards John.

344
00:12:22,324 --> 00:12:23,700
- No.
- No?

345
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:24,617
- Pull it?
- Yes.

346
00:12:24,618 --> 00:12:26,579
Tilt it, but keep it steady.

347
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:28,747
Okay, just a little bit.

348
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:30,331
Oh, no.

349
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:31,291
It has to go that way.

350
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:32,542
- Hold on.
- It's rolling down.

351
00:12:32,543 --> 00:12:34,252
Block it.

352
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:36,004
QUICK BLOCK

353
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:37,755
- Here…
- Yes?

354
00:12:37,756 --> 00:12:39,799
We have to pivot it this way.

355
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:40,967
- Are you sure?
- Got it?

356
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:42,218
It has to go in that direction.

357
00:12:42,219 --> 00:12:44,304
Then, should we try
to push it to the wall?

358
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:45,930
Let's stay by the wall.

359
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:47,265
Gently.

360
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:48,558
It's off-balance.

361
00:12:48,559 --> 00:12:50,351
Gabee, pull tighter.

362
00:12:50,352 --> 00:12:53,521
- It's balanced now, right?
- Yes, pull back a bit, Yong-jin.

363
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:54,689
- Okay.
- Go slowly.

364
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,859
Let's tilt it a little bit.

365
00:12:58,235 --> 00:12:59,320
Yong-jin, pull a bit tighter.

366
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:01,070
That's it.

367
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:02,405
- Wait.
- Hold on.

368
00:13:02,406 --> 00:13:05,116
Gabee, pull a bit.

369
00:13:05,117 --> 00:13:06,911
Move slowly this way.

370
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:09,537
- Please.
- My hands are sweating.

371
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:12,415
Everyone, keep your string tight.

372
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:13,375
Wait.

373
00:13:14,376 --> 00:13:15,793
Karina, pull tighter.

374
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:17,170
TAP

375
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:18,171
Please go in.

376
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:22,425
PLEASE WORK

377
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:25,136
SUCCESS AT LAST?

378
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:26,971
Come on. It's almost there.

379
00:13:26,972 --> 00:13:28,973
- Hold on!
- Hold it tight.

380
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:30,975
- Don't let go.
- We just need to…

381
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:32,310
Do not let go. Stay still.

382
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:33,603
- We just have to tap it.
- Okay.

383
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:35,772
A BALL THAT CAME TO A TEASING STOP

384
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:37,441
Karina, you tap it.

385
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:41,194
Karina, loosen up a little bit.

386
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:43,655
- Hold up.
- Loosen it up and pull this way.

387
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:45,740
- Now, lower it.
- Go slowly.

388
00:13:45,741 --> 00:13:47,450
- You have to be really gentle.
- Yes.

389
00:13:47,451 --> 00:13:48,743
We'll miss it otherwise.

390
00:13:48,744 --> 00:13:51,037
- Tap it lightly.
- Be really gentle.

391
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:54,040
- Stay exactly as you are.
- That's right.

392
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:56,584
Don't pull too hard.

393
00:13:56,585 --> 00:13:58,211
- Be gentle.
- Okay.

394
00:13:58,212 --> 00:13:59,754
Don't let it touch the ground.

395
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:01,464
This was so hard.

396
00:14:01,465 --> 00:14:03,091
Please let this be it.

397
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:05,677
- Please.
- Okay.

398
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:08,346
- Be gentle.
- But the angle…

399
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:09,347
Wait a minute.

400
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:11,558
I'm going to put it down.

401
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:13,184
- It's not a bad position.
- It's not.

402
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:15,645
- It's up to you, Do-hoon.
- Okay.

403
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:17,648
- Slowly.
- I'm being really gentle.

404
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,068
Wait a minute.

405
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:44,716
AGENTS OF MYSTERY SEASON 2

406
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:46,093
Wait a minute.

407
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:52,724
AFTER STRUGGLING FOR ONE HOUR AND A HALF

408
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:56,686
FINALLY THE END OF A DARK TUNNEL

409
00:14:56,687 --> 00:15:00,941
UNBRIDLED JOY

410
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:04,444
Everybody, get in here!

411
00:15:04,445 --> 00:15:05,404
Do-hoon!

412
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:09,866
WE DID IT!

413
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:14,370
It was the first time I teared up
from pure joy.

414
00:15:14,371 --> 00:15:17,123
Four years ago, I got a hole-in-one.

415
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:18,374
This was more exciting.

416
00:15:18,375 --> 00:15:20,293
I can't describe it in words.

417
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:23,296
You had to be there
to feel this dopamine rush.

418
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:25,298
It was as if we were the Red Devils.

419
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:27,008
It felt like the 2002 World Cup.

420
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,594
Unbelievable.

421
00:15:29,511 --> 00:15:30,721
You know what?

422
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:34,724
- It was so hard.
- Now that we've done this…

423
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,768
- We became one.
- We're more united.

424
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:39,354
We can do anything.

425
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:40,855
I think I might cry.

426
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:42,274
I'm serious.

427
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:44,817
- Overwhelmed with emotions.
- It's so overwhelming.

428
00:15:44,818 --> 00:15:46,320
I'm actually crying.

429
00:15:46,862 --> 00:15:49,113
But why isn't the mission over?

430
00:15:49,114 --> 00:15:50,573
- No way.
- You can't be serious.

431
00:15:50,574 --> 00:15:52,033
We need to get the other ball in.

432
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:54,077
- No way.
- That can't be it.

433
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:55,662
- That has to be it.
- Really?

434
00:15:55,663 --> 00:15:56,913
Don't tell me.

435
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:58,998
- This can't be.
- Why don't we pull the top off?

436
00:15:58,999 --> 00:16:00,708
ON THE VERGE OF PULLING THE TABLE APART

437
00:16:00,709 --> 00:16:02,835
Nothing happened.

438
00:16:02,836 --> 00:16:06,172
<i>There was something
I'd been trying to ignore.</i>

439
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:09,884
<i>The purple hole and a blue circle.</i>

440
00:16:09,885 --> 00:16:11,678
The mission wasn't over.

441
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:14,138
We've put this here.

442
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:15,807
What's this?

443
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:18,434
Oh, we can slot it in and lift it.

444
00:16:18,435 --> 00:16:20,478
- Slot it in?
- Do you see the lines?

445
00:16:20,479 --> 00:16:22,689
- Slot it in, slide it, and lift it.
- You're right.

446
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:25,149
SECOND MISSION
USE THE HOOK TO OPEN THE MINI DOOR

447
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:26,192
I think that's it.

448
00:16:26,193 --> 00:16:27,694
The red ball was level one.

449
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:29,445
- This door is level two.
- It's level two.

450
00:16:29,446 --> 00:16:31,322
Okay, let's think of it that way.

451
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:34,742
- This is the easy stuff, right?
- Yes, let go a bit.

452
00:16:34,743 --> 00:16:35,910
- Should I pull closer?
- Pull it.

453
00:16:35,911 --> 00:16:37,245
If we tilt it like earlier…

454
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:38,913
You think this is hard?

455
00:16:38,914 --> 00:16:40,164
- Right?
- We got the ball in.

456
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:43,167
This is a piece of cake.

457
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:44,544
It's easier than the ball.

458
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:45,461
Is this right?

459
00:16:45,462 --> 00:16:46,462
It has to go closer.

460
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:47,881
Karina, pull tighter.

461
00:16:48,465 --> 00:16:50,049
We did it. It's in.

462
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:52,176
- We're really good at this.
- We are.

463
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:55,638
We're so good at this. It's crazy.

464
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:57,181
We'll be able to eat food with this.

465
00:16:57,182 --> 00:16:59,475
A POTENTIAL UTENSIL

466
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:01,019
We're not far off.

467
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:04,063
If there's a contest for this, we'd win.

468
00:17:04,064 --> 00:17:05,523
- We would.
- We would.

469
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:06,941
Bring it on.

470
00:17:06,942 --> 00:17:08,444
Can we actually compete?

471
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:10,362
This is so funny.

472
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:12,947
- It's in.
- It's in.

473
00:17:12,948 --> 00:17:15,867
- Gabee, pull tighter.
- It got in.

474
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:17,785
- Is it in?
- Yes.

475
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:18,912
- It's really in?
- It's in.

476
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:20,872
- Lift it up.
- Lift it.

477
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:22,373
- Gently.
- Move slowly.

478
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:24,251
Three, two, one.

479
00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:26,544
DOOR OPENED IN 5 MINUTES

480
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,005
Something came out!

481
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,592
- Wait, why…
- There's another one!

482
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:35,762
- Why is this one blue?
- What?

483
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:37,972
I think it has to go on the blue circle.

484
00:17:37,973 --> 00:17:40,808
I wasn't worried
since we'd done it before.

485
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:41,851
- Unbelievable.
- It goes there?

486
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:42,852
Isn't this easy?

487
00:17:42,853 --> 00:17:45,063
We've done the hardest part.

488
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:46,856
Okay, let's do this.

489
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:47,691
We've got this!

490
00:17:48,233 --> 00:17:49,151
Don't lose heart.

491
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:51,235
Take it slowly.

492
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:52,320
Here we go.

493
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:54,363
ALREADY AT THE SLOPE

494
00:17:54,364 --> 00:17:56,450
Can you let go a bit at the back?

495
00:17:57,618 --> 00:17:58,618
It's rising.

496
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:01,162
- We're doing well, right?
- It might roll down.

497
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:03,873
- Oh, no.
- Let's… Wait.

498
00:18:03,874 --> 00:18:06,125
- Stop.
- We have to lower it.

499
00:18:06,126 --> 00:18:08,253
STRESSED

500
00:18:08,837 --> 00:18:10,671
- It's good now.
- We did it.

501
00:18:10,672 --> 00:18:12,256
Okay, that's good.

502
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:14,634
- Don't let it go slack.
- Don't let it slack.

503
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:16,804
Should we pull it
towards John and Do-hoon?

504
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:22,350
Now, move it this way.

505
00:18:22,351 --> 00:18:24,311
- Pull a bit tighter, Gabee.
- Just a bit.

506
00:18:27,314 --> 00:18:28,773
We're fucked.

507
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:30,650
What did you say?

508
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:32,527
It's hard to get the ball out of there.

509
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:34,529
This is driving me crazy.

510
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:36,531
Viewers won't get why this is so hard.

511
00:18:36,532 --> 00:18:37,532
- Right?
- I know.

512
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:39,993
If they tried it,
they'd know that this is really annoying.

513
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:45,706
Viewers won't get
why it was so challenging.

514
00:18:45,707 --> 00:18:47,917
But if we open a pop-up store,

515
00:18:47,918 --> 00:18:50,503
this game has to be included.

516
00:18:50,504 --> 00:18:52,755
I wish the fans could try it.

517
00:18:52,756 --> 00:18:54,507
It has to be exactly the same.

518
00:18:54,508 --> 00:18:55,633
