00:29:58,755 --> 00:30:00,172
I'm great at solving puzzles.

780
00:30:00,173 --> 00:30:01,256
Why am I so good at this?

781
00:30:01,257 --> 00:30:03,717
When it comes to things like this,

782
00:30:03,718 --> 00:30:06,011
it's way more satisfying

783
00:30:06,012 --> 00:30:08,764
to solve a problem with your mind
than with your body.

784
00:30:08,765 --> 00:30:12,434
It felt way better
than cranking to get the ball in.

785
00:30:12,435 --> 00:30:16,480
YONG-JIN CHEERING LIKE CRAZY OVER THE BALL

786
00:30:16,481 --> 00:30:20,109
Since I solved it,
I felt like I'd done my part for the day.

787
00:30:21,444 --> 00:30:25,072
Why can't we figure it out?
I feel like we're close.

788
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:26,783
I can't see anything that could work.

789
00:30:27,492 --> 00:30:29,868
<i>We got stuck on the second puzzle.</i>

790
00:30:29,869 --> 00:30:31,746
I couldn't see a solution,
no matter how hard I looked.

791
00:30:32,330 --> 00:30:35,583
The two As are throwing me off.

792
00:30:36,167 --> 00:30:39,211
This can't be as hard
as getting that ball in.

793
00:30:39,212 --> 00:30:40,630
You're right.

794
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:43,258
I really want to solve it.

795
00:30:43,758 --> 00:30:45,092
WELLING UP

796
00:30:45,093 --> 00:30:49,055
I was bad at math as a child.

797
00:30:49,639 --> 00:30:51,598
My mom paid 600,000 won for math tutoring,

798
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:54,269
but I only scored 60, so she gave up.

799
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:59,774
B minus four equals A.

800
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:02,234
That's a good start.

801
00:31:02,235 --> 00:31:05,071
What next? B minus…

802
00:31:06,114 --> 00:31:07,323
It equals four?

803
00:31:12,412 --> 00:31:13,579
I've got it.

804
00:31:13,580 --> 00:31:15,163
- You have? Really?
- Yes.

805
00:31:15,164 --> 00:31:17,916
Our Do-hoon has an extraordinary mind.

806
00:31:17,917 --> 00:31:20,210
Do-hoon came to the rescue again.

807
00:31:20,211 --> 00:31:24,089
- Three times A minus one is eight.
- Three times A?

808
00:31:24,090 --> 00:31:25,716
- You're right.
- That makes eight.

809
00:31:25,717 --> 00:31:27,051
- Right. Three times A is nine.
- Yes.

810
00:31:37,312 --> 00:31:39,187
You look like a math genius.

811
00:31:39,188 --> 00:31:40,522
That works, Do-hoon.

812
00:31:40,523 --> 00:31:41,607
- We did it.
- We did it.

813
00:31:41,608 --> 00:31:43,233
Q-06
MISSION SUCCESSFUL

814
00:31:43,234 --> 00:31:44,401
Great job, Do-hoon.

815
00:31:44,402 --> 00:31:47,487
The key was multiplication.
I'm so impressed.

816
00:31:47,488 --> 00:31:48,989
You're so good at this.

817
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:51,909
The Wagon Brothers saved everyone
in the math room.

818
00:31:51,910 --> 00:31:55,662
<i>My heart was racing when I slid the tiles
and solved the formula.</i>

819
00:31:55,663 --> 00:31:57,123
It was such a dopamine high.

820
00:31:58,958 --> 00:32:00,751
- Okay.
- The key was multiplying it.

821
00:32:00,752 --> 00:32:01,669
That was great.

822
00:32:03,588 --> 00:32:05,547
Let's move onto the next room.

823
00:32:05,548 --> 00:32:06,840
There's nothing.

824
00:32:06,841 --> 00:32:08,134
There's nothing?

825
00:32:12,055 --> 00:32:12,889
Oh, my!

826
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:14,474
Oh, my!

827
00:32:24,525 --> 00:32:26,652
<i>The mouse had something in its mouth.</i>

828
00:32:26,653 --> 00:32:30,113
<i>It looked like blood
or something sticky was trailing out.</i>

829
00:32:30,114 --> 00:32:32,950
It was kind of unsettling.

830
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:36,746
All the videos were strangely chilling.

831
00:32:41,918 --> 00:32:43,251
It must be an experiment.

832
00:32:43,252 --> 00:32:45,672
- You're right.
- They're experimenting on live mice.

833
00:32:46,631 --> 00:32:48,424
What's that?

834
00:32:48,925 --> 00:32:50,051
What's happening?

835
00:32:51,761 --> 00:32:52,971
What's that?

836
00:32:54,347 --> 00:32:55,181
What's happening?

837
00:32:55,765 --> 00:32:57,767
Is it the door to the next room?

838
00:33:02,397 --> 00:33:03,606
Wait, what is this?

839
00:33:05,942 --> 00:33:06,943
What is it?

840
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:09,237
This is the Log-in Room.

841
00:33:10,571 --> 00:33:11,989
You're right.

842
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:13,992
- We're back?
- It's the Log-in Room?

843
00:33:14,575 --> 00:33:15,784
What on earth?

844
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:17,160
<i>What could it be?</i>

845
00:33:17,161 --> 00:33:20,580
We were surprised
we could move between the two rooms.

846
00:33:20,581 --> 00:33:26,795
So, I realized
the other rooms might also be connected.

847
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:28,338
Do we need to scan again?

848
00:33:28,339 --> 00:33:30,716
- Okay.
- Why are we back here?

849
00:33:30,717 --> 00:33:32,134
This room smells nice.

850
00:33:32,135 --> 00:33:34,386
<i>- Hello.</i>
- Hello.

851
00:33:34,387 --> 00:33:38,390
<i>Your security status
has entered the warning phase.</i>

852
00:33:38,391 --> 00:33:42,185
<i>The Trackers will pursue you
more fiercely and quickly.</i>

853
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:43,562
- Oh, no.
- What do we do?

854
00:33:43,563 --> 00:33:44,938
<i>For your safety,</i>

855
00:33:44,939 --> 00:33:46,648
<i>the next security check</i>

856
00:33:46,649 --> 00:33:48,984
<i>will require you
to split up into two parties.</i>

857
00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:53,071
<i>Please complete the security check
in two groups of three.</i>

858
00:33:53,072 --> 00:33:55,365
- There are two rooms.
<i>- From now on,</i>

859
00:33:55,366 --> 00:33:57,617
<i>you must move between rooms
as quietly as possible.</i>

860
00:33:57,618 --> 00:34:00,204
- This is bad.
- How should we split up?

861
00:34:01,497 --> 00:34:02,914
- What's that?
- What's that?

862
00:34:02,915 --> 00:34:03,999
It must be for the next room.

863
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:05,334
- Are there two cards?
- Yes.

864
00:34:05,835 --> 00:34:08,003
<i>I was worried.</i>

865
00:34:08,004 --> 00:34:10,964
It was already hard solving it together.

866
00:34:10,965 --> 00:34:13,843
How would we manage if we split up?

867
00:34:14,802 --> 00:34:16,553
How should we split up?

868
00:34:16,554 --> 00:34:18,138
- Should we do "palms up or down"?
- Okay.

869
00:34:18,139 --> 00:34:20,348
Should we do men and women?

870
00:34:20,349 --> 00:34:21,475
I'm not sure about that.

871
00:34:21,476 --> 00:34:23,018
- I think a mix is better.
- Okay.

872
00:34:23,019 --> 00:34:25,312
- And think of the viewers.
- Then…

873
00:34:25,313 --> 00:34:27,230
- Who would want to watch just us?
- That's fair.

874
00:34:27,231 --> 00:34:29,649
We need to split us up a bit.

875
00:34:29,650 --> 00:34:30,734
Let's do this.

876
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:33,321
<i>- Palm ups or down
- Palm ups or down</i>

877
00:34:33,821 --> 00:34:35,947
THE TIMING IS MESSED UP

878
00:34:35,948 --> 00:34:37,574
In Gyeonggi-do,
we sing "flip it up or down."

879
00:34:37,575 --> 00:34:39,951
<i>-Palms up or down
- Dedenjji</i>

880
00:34:39,952 --> 00:34:41,912
<i>-Dedenjji</i>
- What do you use?

881
00:34:41,913 --> 00:34:43,872
I say "<i>dedenjji</i>" or "palms up or down."

882
00:34:43,873 --> 00:34:45,082
- I use "<i>dedenjji</i>" too.
- And Gabee?

883
00:34:45,083 --> 00:34:46,166
<i>Palms up or down</i>

884
00:34:46,167 --> 00:34:48,919
<i>Too bad if it gets stuck
Have the baby in a toilet</i>

885
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:49,878
Have a baby in what?

886
00:34:49,879 --> 00:34:51,505
Have the baby in a toilet.

887
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:52,881
It's so vulgar.

888
00:34:52,882 --> 00:34:54,216
The poor baby.

889
00:34:54,217 --> 00:34:55,467
I think that's how it goes.

890
00:34:55,468 --> 00:34:57,260
- That's how I learned it.
- A baby in a toilet?

891
00:34:57,261 --> 00:34:59,012
Can we use your version's melody?

892
00:34:59,013 --> 00:35:01,140
<i>- Palms up or down
- Palms up or down</i>

893
00:35:02,558 --> 00:35:04,101
Is this fate?

894
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:06,103
- No way.
- Go again?

895
00:35:06,104 --> 00:35:07,438
<i>Palms up or down</i>

896
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:11,817
It's good.

897
00:35:11,818 --> 00:35:13,485
Should we pick blue or red, Gabee?

898
00:35:13,486 --> 00:35:14,695
- Let's go with blue.
- Okay.

899
00:35:15,655 --> 00:35:16,614
I'll keep this.

900
00:35:17,281 --> 00:35:18,698
Everyone, quiet.

901
00:35:18,699 --> 00:35:21,493
EVERYONE, BE CAREFUL OF THE TRACKERS

902
00:35:21,494 --> 00:35:23,663
Plus, we need to solve it quickly.

903
00:35:24,664 --> 00:35:25,540
Ready to go?

904
00:35:31,712 --> 00:35:34,256
RED TEAM: ROOM 106

905
00:35:34,257 --> 00:35:36,591
BLUE TEAM: ROOM 211

906
00:35:36,592 --> 00:35:38,593
RUN BEFORE THE TRACKERS COME

907
00:35:38,594 --> 00:35:40,763
THEY MUST SOLVE THE PUZZLES FIRST

908
00:35:43,558 --> 00:35:45,600
DIFFERENT BUT SIMILAR TWIN PUZZLES

909
00:35:45,601 --> 00:35:47,310
THE KEY CARDS ARE RED AND BLUE

910
00:35:47,311 --> 00:35:49,896
There are numbers here.

911
00:35:49,897 --> 00:35:51,774
That must be it.

912
00:35:53,484 --> 00:35:55,236
WHEN THE CARD IS PLACED ON THE PUZZLE

913
00:35:55,903 --> 00:35:59,323
IT CLEARLY SAYS ZERO

914
00:36:01,909 --> 00:36:03,035
Eight.

915
00:36:04,537 --> 00:36:05,705
What is it?

916
00:36:12,962 --> 00:36:13,796
That's wrong.

917
00:36:15,506 --> 00:36:17,716
FOUND THE "N" THEY MISSED

918
00:36:17,717 --> 00:36:19,427
Try 9720.

919
00:36:20,219 --> 00:36:21,053
Okay.

920
00:36:24,432 --> 00:36:25,266
Let's go.

921
00:36:32,064 --> 00:36:34,066
Oh, my. What's all this?

922
00:36:35,234 --> 00:36:37,152
Is it a kind of maze?

923
00:36:37,153 --> 00:36:41,406
MYSTERIOUS PATTERNED CUBES

924
00:36:41,407 --> 00:36:43,034
- Is it like a puzzle?
- I think so.

925
00:36:44,452 --> 00:36:46,036
This is scary.

926
00:36:46,037 --> 00:36:47,245
Hey, this is…

927
00:36:47,246 --> 00:36:48,246
I can't see anything.

928
00:36:48,247 --> 00:36:50,208
I think we have to do this in the dark.

929
00:36:50,708 --> 00:36:52,667
There was some kind of puzzle.

930
00:36:52,668 --> 00:36:55,670
<i>As we were getting started,
the lights suddenly went off.</i>

931
00:36:55,671 --> 00:36:58,006
- I can't see a thing.
- Me neither.

932
00:36:58,007 --> 00:37:00,467
ROOM 211 TEAM ENTERS

933
00:37:00,468 --> 00:37:02,093
A MICROPHONE ON A TABLE

934
00:37:02,094 --> 00:37:03,721
Wait, what is that?

935
00:37:04,305 --> 00:37:06,139
We can see them.
We must have to work together.

936
00:37:06,140 --> 00:37:07,057
THE MONITOR SHOWS THE RED TEAM

937
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:10,852
There was a monitor and a microphone.

938
00:37:10,853 --> 00:37:12,062
Can you hear us?

939
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:13,064
Wait, try again.

940
00:37:13,564 --> 00:37:15,649
Can you hear us?

941
00:37:15,650 --> 00:37:17,150
<i>Can you hear us?</i>

942
00:37:17,151 --> 00:37:18,318
Yes!

943
00:37:18,319 --> 00:37:19,570
Isn't that Gabee's voice?

944
00:37:20,071 --> 00:37:21,196
Can you hear us?

945
00:37:21,197 --> 00:37:22,698
Can you see us from there?

946
00:37:23,616 --> 00:37:26,576
We can't hear you.

947
00:37:26,577 --> 00:37:28,329
Use gestures.

948
00:37:31,457 --> 00:37:33,959
I don't think they can see.

949
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:36,378
- It must be dark in there.
- I get it! You're in the dark.

950
00:37:36,379 --> 00:37:38,672
- We have to guide them.
- Sorry.

951
00:37:38,673 --> 00:37:40,924
It was an infrared camera.

952
00:37:40,925 --> 00:37:43,885
That meant they had
to solve something in the dark.

953
00:37:43,886 --> 00:37:47,097
We needed to guide them with explanations.

954
00:37:47,098 --> 00:37:50,268
I guess we have to solve it
by doing as they say.

955
00:37:51,102 --> 00:37:52,477
How do we solve that?

956
00:37:52,478 --> 00:37:53,436
- Well…
- Now…

957
00:37:53,437 --> 00:37:55,563
- Let's bring them together.
- Bunch them together.

958
00:37:55,564 --> 00:38:01,152
Sorry, but could you gather
all the cubes into the center?

959
00:38:01,153 --> 00:38:04,155
THE CUBES LOOK TOO SPREAD OUT
ON THE MONITOR

960
00:38:04,156 --> 00:38:06,866
It must be a night-vision lens.

961
00:38:06,867 --> 00:38:07,868
I guess so.

962
00:38:09,912 --> 00:38:10,996
Okay.

963
00:38:10,997 --> 00:38:16,459
You can kind of see
the bright parts on the cushions.

964
00:38:16,460 --> 00:38:19,087
So, there's a cushion here.

965
00:38:19,088 --> 00:38:20,463
There's another one here.

966
00:38:20,464 --> 00:38:23,968
Let's give it a go.

967
00:38:27,555 --> 00:38:29,347
<i>-Yes, that's great.</i>
- Like this?

968
00:38:29,348 --> 00:38:32,100
- I'll push it up.
- Okay.

969
00:38:32,101 --> 00:38:33,311
Push them together, right?

970
00:38:35,438 --> 00:38:37,898
- How do we solve this?
- This is hard.

971
00:38:41,861 --> 00:38:42,862
What is it?

972
00:38:44,864 --> 00:38:45,823
What is it?

973
00:38:46,449 --> 00:38:48,075
Why? Is someone else in there?

974
00:38:48,909 --> 00:38:49,827
Yong-jin.

975
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:51,162
Who is it?

976
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:53,664
- Someone's in here!
- I know.

977
00:38:54,373 --> 00:38:55,583
I hate this.

978
00:39:03,007 --> 00:39:04,007
Why do this?

979
00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:06,302
- Let's gather over here.
- This is…

980
00:39:06,927 --> 00:39:08,303
I hate this so much.

981
00:39:08,304 --> 00:39:09,472
Come this way.

982
00:39:10,181 --> 00:39:14,100
SOMEONE ELSE IS IN HERE

983
00:39:14,101 --> 00:39:16,728
<i>All of a sudden, we weren't alone.</i>

984
00:39:16,729 --> 00:39:18,981
I thought of the ghost
we saw in the other room.

985
00:39:20,608 --> 00:39:22,067
I thought it was back.

986
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:24,402
A ghost was coming for us in the dark.

987
00:39:24,403 --> 00:39:25,613
Are you all okay?

988
00:39:26,697 --> 00:39:28,616
We can't see anything at all.

989
00:39:29,909 --> 00:39:31,868
- They left, right?
- No.

990
00:39:31,869 --> 00:39:33,119
- They're over there.
- They are?

991
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:34,037
They're moving.

992
00:39:34,038 --> 00:39:35,039
JOHN MAKES A BOLD MOVE

993
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:39,417
- I think they've gone now.
- Yes.

994
00:39:39,418 --> 00:39:41,169
I think they left.

995
00:39:41,170 --> 00:39:42,630
<i>Are you all okay?</i>

996
00:39:43,214 --> 00:39:45,340
Use your hands to make an O or X.

997
00:39:45,341 --> 00:39:47,467
<i>- So, you're okay?</i>
- Yes.

998
00:39:47,468 --> 00:39:50,595
Can you move the second cube
to the far right bottom?

999
00:39:50,596 --> 00:39:52,222
<i>- It's the one</i>
- Which one's the second one?

1000
00:39:52,223 --> 00:39:53,640
<i>that's two over from Yong-jin.</i>

1001
00:39:53,641 --> 00:39:55,642
But what about the person
who was just here?

1002
00:39:55,643 --> 00:39:56,685
Is that the end of it?

1003
00:39:57,269 --> 00:40:00,605
It's the cube
that's two over from Yong-jin.

1004
00:40:00,606 --> 00:40:03,275
- To the right…
<i>- No, go back, Karina.</i>

1005
00:40:04,026 --> 00:40:07,071
<i>That's it.
Now, move it to the very bottom.</i>

1006
00:40:07,696 --> 00:40:08,781
This is too hard.

1007
00:40:11,325 --> 00:40:13,119
All right.

1008
00:40:13,828 --> 00:40:15,537
Wait a minute.

1009
00:40:15,538 --> 00:40:17,705
- My head hurts.
- It's okay.

1010
00:40:17,706 --> 00:40:18,790
Let's take our time.

1011
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:21,252
I think they need time to figure it out.

1012
00:40:21,794 --> 00:40:24,504
- But we can see a little bit too.
- Right?

1013
00:40:24,505 --> 00:40:25,964
- We can make it out.
- Yes.

1014
00:40:25,965 --> 00:40:27,507
I think my eyes have adjusted.

1015
00:40:27,508 --> 00:40:29,343
- Should we give it a go?
- Yes.

1016
00:40:30,219 --> 00:40:32,762
All right. To start off with…

1017
00:40:32,763 --> 00:40:34,556
These go on the outside, right?

1018
00:40:34,557 --> 00:40:35,473
- Yes.
- Yes.

1019
00:40:35,474 --> 00:40:37,308
So, let's move them to the side.

1020
00:40:37,309 --> 00:40:38,394
TAKES OUT THE OUTER CUBES

1021
00:40:41,147 --> 00:40:44,984
- I think they can see a little.
- Yes, they've adjusted.

1022
00:40:49,321 --> 00:40:51,490
THE CHOKER LIGHTS TURN OFF

1023
00:40:52,908 --> 00:40:54,659
- Karina.
- We can't see even a little?

1024
00:40:54,660 --> 00:40:55,660
That's so harsh.

1025
00:40:55,661 --> 00:40:57,496
- Can you reach out?
- I'm right here.

1026
00:40:59,665 --> 00:41:01,124
It was pitch black.

1027
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:03,502
We couldn't see
what was right in front of us.

1028
00:41:04,795 --> 00:41:05,962
I can't see at all.

1029
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:07,297
I can't see a thing.

1030
00:41:07,298 --> 00:41:08,966
- Are all the cubes at the center?
- Yes.

1031
00:41:09,758 --> 00:41:12,218
They turned the chokers off.

1032
00:41:12,219 --> 00:41:14,805
I couldn't see Yong-jin
right in front of me.

1033
00:41:17,183 --> 00:41:18,808
FUMBLING

1034
00:41:18,809 --> 00:41:19,976
I see nothing.

1035
00:41:19,977 --> 00:41:20,935
On your right…

1036
00:41:20,936 --> 00:41:22,730
They can't see anything.

1037
00:41:24,106 --> 00:41:27,108
If there's an F1 key,
they might need to press it.

1038
00:41:27,109 --> 00:41:28,735
Right? We can't see anything.

1039
00:41:28,736 --> 00:41:32,072
Yong-jin, can you move
the cube to your right down a little?

1040
00:41:32,823 --> 00:41:34,073
Yong-jin.

1041
00:41:34,074 --> 00:41:35,201
Someone came in.

1042
00:41:36,535 --> 00:41:37,912
Someone just came in.

1043
00:41:41,415 --> 00:41:42,833
Are you okay?

1044
00:41:43,334 --> 00:41:44,210
No.

1045
00:41:46,712 --> 00:41:48,255
I can't see at all.

1046
00:41:50,341 --> 00:41:51,300
<i>Someone's there.</i>

1047
00:41:52,384 --> 00:41:53,843
Someone's there.

1048
00:41:53,844 --> 00:41:56,555
Shouldn't we tell them?

1049
00:41:57,389 --> 00:41:59,350
- They're dressed like us.
- They are.

1050
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:01,893
- Move back.
- They're coming this way.

1051
00:42:01,894 --> 00:42:02,895
Come back this way.

1052
00:42:03,521 --> 00:42:05,355
- They're coming.
- Where are you, Yong-jin?

1053
00:42:05,356 --> 00:42:06,607
Come this way.

1054
00:42:07,566 --> 00:42:09,651
- Where are you, John?
- I'm here.

1055
00:42:09,652 --> 00:42:12,238
- Are they right in front of us?
- I think they are.

1056
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:15,658
This is…

1057
00:42:17,743 --> 00:42:19,077
JOHN STEPS FORWARD

1058
00:42:19,078 --> 00:42:20,788
Where are you going?

1059
00:42:21,789 --> 00:42:22,831
Who are you?

1060
00:42:24,458 --> 00:42:26,377
That person looks scared.

1061
00:42:28,963 --> 00:42:29,922
Who is it?

1062
00:42:30,881 --> 00:42:32,174
They look normal.

1063
00:42:33,676 --> 00:42:35,218
Who are you?

1064
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:36,220
What's going on?

1065
00:42:37,346 --> 00:42:39,598
- They're not saying anything either.
- Right?

1066
00:42:40,307 --> 00:42:43,101
THEY ARE SPEECHLESS

1067
00:42:43,102 --> 00:42:45,229
<i>Since we couldn't hear them,</i>

1068
00:42:45,854 --> 00:42:49,441
<i>we had no idea
what was going on or how to help.</i>

1069
00:42:50,192 --> 00:42:54,530
We weren't sure if we should say anything
because of the intruder.

1070
00:42:55,114 --> 00:42:56,532
Are you okay?

1071
00:42:57,950 --> 00:42:58,867
No.

1072
00:42:59,451 --> 00:43:01,077
Have they left?

1073
00:43:01,078 --> 00:43:02,328
Let's stay back and stick together.

1074
00:43:02,329 --> 00:43:03,997
- I can't even see if they left.
- Me neither.

1075
00:43:03,998 --> 00:43:05,123
I can't see anything.

1076
00:43:05,124 --> 00:43:06,041
I'm right here, John.

1077
00:43:06,709 --> 00:43:08,335
Are you okay, Yong-jin?

1078
00:43:09,169 --> 00:43:12,505
Stomp your right foot twice
if you're okay.

1079
00:43:12,506 --> 00:43:13,757
I'm not okay.

1080
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:15,800
STOMP

1081
00:43:15,801 --> 00:43:16,677
What was that?

1082
00:43:18,095 --> 00:43:19,471
That wasn't us.

1083
00:43:21,473 --> 00:43:22,391
What the heck?

1084
00:43:23,309 --> 00:43:24,309
What was that?

1085
00:43:24,310 --> 00:43:25,560
Where are you? Who is this?

1086
00:43:25,561 --> 00:43:27,437
- It's me, Karina.
- I'm right here.

1087
00:43:27,438 --> 00:43:31,150
I was losing my mind
because it was so dark.

1088
00:43:31,942 --> 00:43:33,235
We could only hear noises.

1089
00:43:39,658 --> 00:43:41,827
FROZEN IN PLACE

1090
00:43:45,623 --> 00:43:47,416
- They're still here, right?
- Yes.

1091
00:43:48,208 --> 00:43:50,586
- Can you see?
- Not at all.

1092
00:43:54,381 --> 00:43:56,759
- Can we just let this happen?
- Right?

1093
00:43:57,301 --> 00:43:58,761
Should we help?

1094
00:43:59,928 --> 00:44:03,931
If you need our help, give us a sign.

1095
00:44:03,932 --> 00:44:07,268
<i>Make circles with your arms.</i>

1096
00:44:07,269 --> 00:44:08,186
HELP US

1097
00:44:08,187 --> 00:44:10,313
I don't see any circles.

1098
00:44:10,314 --> 00:44:11,357
I can't see their hands.

1099
00:44:11,899 --> 00:44:13,941
If you need our help,

1100
00:44:13,942 --> 00:44:17,153
bang twice on the top of a cube.

1101
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:18,821
BANG

1102
00:44:18,822 --> 00:44:20,281
CLEAR BANGING

1103
00:44:20,282 --> 00:44:22,241
- They need our help.
- What can we do?

1104
00:44:22,242 --> 00:44:24,160
How can we help them?

1105
00:44:24,161 --> 00:44:27,914
Do we need to hurry solving the puzzle?

1106
00:44:27,915 --> 00:44:30,376
Bang on the cube if that's it.

1107
00:44:30,959 --> 00:44:32,878
WE DON'T KNOW

1108
00:44:33,379 --> 00:44:35,172
What is going on?

1109
00:44:35,798 --> 00:44:38,132
Are they taking the cubes?

1110
00:44:38,133 --> 00:44:39,634
Someone took a cube?

1111
00:44:39,635 --> 00:44:41,594
<i>Hye-ri made a strange comment.</i>

1112
00:44:41,595 --> 00:44:44,597
She said the person was taking a cube.

1113
00:44:44,598 --> 00:44:47,142
<i>It was a strange situation.</i>

1114
00:44:51,897 --> 00:44:54,733
What the heck? Who are you?

1115
00:44:56,151 --> 00:44:57,985
- Is that them, John?
- Who are you?

1116
00:44:57,986 --> 00:44:59,113
Who are you?

1117
00:44:59,696 --> 00:45:00,739
Who are you?

1118
00:45:02,449 --> 00:45:04,034
They're here!

1119
00:45:04,743 --> 00:45:06,870
WHAT IS HAPPENING?

1120
00:45:07,913 --> 00:45:10,040
- Who is it?
- It's me, Yong-jin.

1121
00:45:10,582 --> 00:45:11,958
That's not Yong-jin! Get him!

1122
00:45:11,959 --> 00:45:14,085
- Who are you? I got you!
- Where are they?

1123
00:45:14,086 --> 00:45:15,086
- You got them?
- I got them!

1124
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:16,379
- Where are you?
- I'm over here!

1125
00:45:16,380 --> 00:45:18,047
- Where are you?
- Who are you?

1126
00:45:18,048 --> 00:45:19,841
- Who are you?
- Where are you, John?

1127
00:45:19,842 --> 00:45:21,008
I'm here.

1128
00:45:21,009 --> 00:45:24,345
- Follow my voice.
- We got him.

1129
00:45:24,346 --> 00:45:25,763
- Here.
- No!

1130
00:45:25,764 --> 00:45:26,889
- Who are you?
- We got him.

1131
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:28,433
- Is this him?
- We got him.

1132
00:45:28,434 --> 00:45:30,351
- I got him.
- Yes, we got him.

1133
00:45:30,352 --> 00:45:31,769
- Who are you?
- Who are you?

1134
00:45:31,770 --> 00:45:33,688
- Are you an XIN member?
- Are you here to help?

1135
00:45:33,689 --> 00:45:34,815
I came to help.

1136
00:45:35,482 --> 00:45:36,816
I'm here to help.

1137
00:45:36,817 --> 00:45:37,860
What's your name?

1138
00:45:38,527 --> 00:45:39,444
Lee Yong-jin.

1139
00:45:39,445 --> 00:45:41,195
What are you talking about?

1140
00:45:41,196 --> 00:45:43,990
NO IDEA WHAT'S HAPPENING

1141
00:45:43,991 --> 00:45:44,907
I came to help.

1142
00:45:44,908 --> 00:45:46,826
- Why didn't you say so?
- How did you come here?

1143
00:45:46,827 --> 00:45:48,202
Why didn't you say anything?

1144
00:45:48,203 --> 00:45:50,079
- Why?
- What's wrong with you?

1145
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:51,622
I was scared too.

1146
00:45:51,623 --> 00:45:53,166
- I'm sorry.
- If you came to help…

1147
00:45:53,167 --> 00:45:55,418
- You're really here to help, right?
- I am.

1148
00:45:55,419 --> 00:45:56,961
- How will you help?
- I'm Lee Yong-jin.

1149
00:45:56,962 --> 00:45:57,879
Mr. Yong-jin.

1150
00:45:57,880 --> 00:46:00,339
We caught him.

1151
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:01,966
We caught Mr. Yong-jin.

1152
00:46:01,967 --> 00:46:03,885
He said he came to help.

1153
00:46:03,886 --> 00:46:06,138
And we were told he was dressed like us.

1154
00:46:06,930 --> 00:46:10,057
So, we thought he could be a fellow agent.

1155
00:46:10,058 --> 00:46:12,436
THE FELLOW AGENTS ARE WATCHING
IN THE OTHER ROOM

1156
00:46:13,145 --> 00:46:14,480
I'd be crying in that room.

1157
00:46:14,980 --> 00:46:17,857
Should we hurry up with the puzzle?

1158
00:46:17,858 --> 00:46:18,858
What do we do?

1159
00:46:18,859 --> 00:46:19,859
CONFUSED

1160
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,527
- It's all good.
- Let's solve the puzzle.

1161
00:46:21,528 --> 00:46:22,528
- I'll help you.
- It's okay.

1162
00:46:22,529 --> 00:46:24,155
- I'll go over there.
- Okay.

1163
00:46:24,156 --> 00:46:26,866
You cover that area.

1164
00:46:26,867 --> 00:46:27,783
YONG-JIN 1 AND YONG-JIN 2

1165
00:46:27,784 --> 00:46:29,035
You're really helping us?

1166
00:46:29,036 --> 00:46:31,163
Can you see anything, Mr. Yong-jin?

1167
00:46:31,705 --> 00:46:33,039
- No.
- Are you sitting, Yong-jin?

1168
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:34,081
I am.

1169
00:46:34,082 --> 00:46:36,375
- Let me get past.
- Okay, hang on.

1170
00:46:36,376 --> 00:46:38,002
- Mr. Yong-jin.
- You really scared me.

1171
00:46:38,003 --> 00:46:39,337
Why did you do that, Mr. Yong-jin?

1172
00:46:39,338 --> 00:46:41,589
Karina, you cover this area.
I'll help over there.

1173
00:46:41,590 --> 00:46:43,800
- Do you know the pattern, Mr. Yong-jin?
- I'll help Mr. Yong-jin.

1174
00:46:46,094 --> 00:46:47,220
WHAT NOW?

1175
00:46:47,221 --> 00:46:49,180
What do we need to do?

1176
00:46:49,181 --> 00:46:50,723
Does he keep taking a cube?

1177
00:46:50,724 --> 00:46:52,558
- He's taking a cube?
- This is driving me crazy.

1178
00:46:52,559 --> 00:46:53,894
He's taking a cube?

1179
00:46:54,811 --> 00:46:57,104
- What the heck?
- He must be taking the cubes.

1180
00:46:57,105 --> 00:46:59,815
<i>- We'll hurry with the puzzle.</i>
- He left!

1181
00:46:59,816 --> 00:47:01,526
He must be taking the cubes.

1182
00:47:01,527 --> 00:47:04,028
When we caught him,

1183
00:47:04,029 --> 00:47:05,572
he said his name was Lee Yong-jin.

1184
00:47:06,698 --> 00:47:08,908
I could feel that he was dressed
the same as us.

1185
00:47:08,909 --> 00:47:11,536
He just kept repeating ridiculous things.

1186
00:47:11,537 --> 00:47:13,246
And the other team said

1187
00:47:13,247 --> 00:47:15,039
- he was taking cubes.
- Does he keep taking a cube?

1188
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:15,957
It was pitch black.

1189
00:47:15,958 --> 00:47:18,210
We were scared and frustrated.

1190
00:47:18,794 --> 00:47:20,170
And my bladder was about to burst.

1191
00:47:20,671 --> 00:47:22,296
Let's make a three-way pledge.

1192
00:47:22,297 --> 00:47:24,299
John and Karina, let's make a promise.

1193
00:47:25,050 --> 00:47:26,884
Don't stay silent as a prank.

1194
00:47:26,885 --> 00:47:28,219
- That would be crazy.
- I mean it!

1195
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:29,554
- We won't.
- I'll make you pay!

1196
00:47:29,555 --> 00:47:30,680
- That's nuts.
- I mean it!

1197
00:47:30,681 --> 00:47:31,889
Don't mess around like that.

1198
00:47:31,890 --> 00:47:33,891
- I'll kill anyone who does.
- Same.

1199
00:47:33,892 --> 00:47:35,226
I'll write an official complaint.

1200
00:47:35,227 --> 00:47:36,519
I'm dead serious.

1201
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:39,147
I'll get violent if that happens.

1202
00:47:40,524 --> 00:47:41,608
All right, so…

1203
00:47:42,776 --> 00:47:45,653
Do we need to focus on the black shapes?

1204
00:47:45,654 --> 00:47:47,863
<i>The puzzle was too complicated.</i>

1205
00:47:47,864 --> 00:47:50,533
<i>It was really tricky to solve.</i>

1206
00:47:50,534 --> 00:47:53,829
We needed to use the F1 key.

1207
00:47:54,413 --> 00:47:55,329
Go on.

1208
00:47:55,330 --> 00:47:56,164
DO-HOON STEPS UP

1209
00:48:08,969 --> 00:48:12,139
THEY MUST MATCH THIS IMAGE IN THE DARK

1210
00:48:12,723 --> 00:48:14,849
We need to number them.

1211
00:48:14,850 --> 00:48:16,934
- Let's number the squares.
- Okay.

1212
00:48:16,935 --> 00:48:18,352
<i>That's the one.</i>

1213
00:48:18,353 --> 00:48:20,021
<i>Move it to square two.</i>

1214
00:48:20,022 --> 00:48:21,814
<i>That's it. You just need to…</i>

1215
00:48:21,815 --> 00:48:22,649
<i>Okay.</i>

1216
00:48:33,869 --> 00:48:35,370
- It's nearly complete, right?
- Yes.

1217
00:48:36,163 --> 00:48:37,955
- There are two left.
- I can't see a thing.

1218
00:48:37,956 --> 00:48:39,082
I can't see anything.

1219
00:48:39,916 --> 00:48:40,833
YONG-JIN 2 IS BACK

1220
00:48:40,834 --> 00:48:42,335
Why are you doing this?

1221
00:48:42,336 --> 00:48:43,794
RUNS OFF

1222
00:48:43,795 --> 00:48:44,712
Hey, Yong-jin.

1223
00:48:44,713 --> 00:48:46,715
Mr. Yong-jin.

1224
00:48:48,091 --> 00:48:51,844
- He's at it again.
- Why is he doing this?

1225
00:48:51,845 --> 00:48:52,762
Yong-jin.

1226
00:48:52,763 --> 00:48:54,722
That really scared me.

1227
00:48:54,723 --> 00:48:55,640
Are you okay, Yong-jin?

1228
00:48:55,641 --> 00:48:56,975
Where are you?

1229
00:48:58,560 --> 00:48:59,560
SIGHS

1230
00:48:59,561 --> 00:49:01,979
I really hate to admit it.

1231
00:49:01,980 --> 00:49:03,022
But I was terrified.

1232
00:49:03,023 --> 00:49:04,106
Are you okay, Yong-jin?

1233
00:49:04,107 --> 00:49:06,233
<i>- The cube on the left…</i>
- I'm on the ground.

1234
00:49:06,234 --> 00:49:08,444
<i>I mean the one that's been left out.</i>

1235
00:49:08,445 --> 00:49:10,029
Can't they see what's going on?

1236
00:49:10,030 --> 00:49:11,364
<i>It's square 11.</i>

1237
00:49:11,365 --> 00:49:12,990
I even tripped while running away.

1238
00:49:12,991 --> 00:49:15,077
But while I was falling over,

1239
00:49:15,661 --> 00:49:18,163
- she was going on about square 11.
- <i>It's square 11.</i>

1240
00:49:18,705 --> 00:49:21,624
We need to do a role reversal.

1241
00:49:21,625 --> 00:49:22,625
Yong-jin.

1242
00:49:22,626 --> 00:49:23,627
1 MINUTE AGO

1243
00:49:28,423 --> 00:49:29,757
We need to hurry with the puzzle.

1244
00:49:29,758 --> 00:49:32,176
The cube on the left…

1245
00:49:32,177 --> 00:49:34,720
- I mean the one that's left out.
- The one left out.

1246
00:49:34,721 --> 00:49:36,431
Once, twice…

1247
00:49:39,476 --> 00:49:40,810
Great job!

1248
00:49:40,811 --> 00:49:42,562
That's right. Great job.

1249
00:49:43,230 --> 00:49:44,939
You did great.

1250
00:49:44,940 --> 00:49:47,900
FREE AT LAST?

1251
00:49:47,901 --> 00:49:49,652
SUCCESSFUL

1252
00:49:49,653 --> 00:49:52,030
ESCAPE FROM THE DARK

1253
00:49:53,156 --> 00:49:55,492
- I'm not built for this.
- My eyes hurt.

1254
00:49:56,284 --> 00:49:58,035
SURPRISED

1255
00:49:58,036 --> 00:50:00,287
PROTECTIVE INSTINCT

1256
00:50:00,288 --> 00:50:01,789
I'm so scared.

1257
00:50:01,790 --> 00:50:03,249
That scared me.

1258
00:50:03,250 --> 00:50:06,460
That was really challenging.

1259
00:50:06,461 --> 00:50:08,045
- Let's go.
- The next room is 215.

1260
00:50:08,046 --> 00:50:09,422
Hold up.

1261
00:50:09,423 --> 00:50:10,798
Let's study this first.

1262
00:50:10,799 --> 00:50:12,258
- It's just black.
- Let's just go.

1263
00:50:12,259 --> 00:50:13,175
A PLAIN BLACK KEY CARD

1264
00:50:13,176 --> 00:50:14,594
We need to solve the puzzle quickly.

1265
00:51:48,855 --> 00:51:53,860
Subtitle translation by: Hannah Og Nam
